Problem Statement

You are given an array A of length N and two functions:
1. frequency(left, right, value): Returns the number of elements in the range [left, right] that are equal to value.
2. distinct(left, right): Returns the number of distinct elements in the range [left, right].

Find the number of pairs (i, j) where 1 <= i < j <= N that satisfy:
frequency(1, i, A[i]) + frequency(j, N, A[j]) <= floor(distinct(1, i) / 2) + floor(distinct(j, N) / 2)

Since the answer can be very large, return it modulo 10^9 + 7.

Constraints
1 <= N <= 10^5
1 <= A[i] <= 10^9

